-#          which discards most of the real sensor range (0–40952).  Corrected to
-#          the actual hardware range.  PPG guard widened to 40–200 bpm.
-#
-#   FIX-D  EEG RANGE: original code required EEG >= 0 but many band-power
-#          columns normalised to 0–1.  Guard now between(0.0, 1.0); if the CSV
-#          stores raw counts (> 1) the guard is auto-bypassed.
-#
-#   FIX-E  EPOCH COUNT / EARLY STOPPING:
-#            • EarlyStopping patience raised so training actually runs long enough
-#              (patience=30 for sensor, patience=30 for facial, patience=20 for
-#              predictor) — the original patience=15/20 caused the 18-epoch stop.
-#            • min_delta lowered to 0.0001 so tiny improvements keep training going.
-#            • restore_best_weights=True on all three models.
-#
-#   FIX-F  COSINE LR (FIX-1 from v1): CosineDecay is passed INTO Adam() at
-#          creation, not re-assigned after compile().
-#
-#   FIX-G  SMOTE ORDER (FIX-2 from v1): SMOTE applied BEFORE train/val split.
-#
-#   FIX-H  FACIAL steps_per_epoch (FIX-3 from v1): explicitly set so Keras
-#          knows epoch boundaries when using a generator.
-#
-#   FIX-I  FUTURE PREDICTOR always runs as long as the sensor model saved
-#          scaler.pkl — even when the sensor model itself was not returned by
-#          the current run (e.g. loaded from a previous run).
-#
-#   FIX-J  CLASS WEIGHTS applied to sensor AND facial training.
-#
-#   FIX-K  DATA VALIDATION REPORT: prints a clear diagnostics table before
-#          training so you can immediately see why the CSV may have been rejected.
-#
-#   FIX-L  .xls support: uses xlrd to read old-format Excel files (the original
-#          path ends in .xls but pd.read_csv was called — this silently failed).
-# """
