+# """
+# MENTAL HEALTH ASSESSMENT — UNIFIED TRAINING SCRIPT (FINAL FIXED)
+# =================================================================
+# Trains in order:
+#   1) Sensor RNN      (BiLSTM + GRU + Attention)       — 6 mental states
+#   2) Facial CNN      (Residual CNN, 7 emotions)
+#   3) Future Predictor (Seq2Seq BiLSTM + Attention)    — 5-step sensor forecast
+#
+# ROOT CAUSE FIXES (why sensor CSV was skipped & epochs stopped early):
+# ──────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
+#   FIX-A  CSV ENCODING: pd.read_csv() with multi-encoding fallback so the
+#          sensor CSV is never silently skipped. Also handles both .csv and
+#          .xls extensions (xlrd for old .xls, openpyxl for .xlsx).
+#
+#   FIX-B  COLUMN NORMALISATION: strips whitespace and maps common alternate
+#          column names (e.g. "label" → "Label", "Heart Rate" → "PPG") so the
+#          CSV is not rejected on a missing-column check.
+#
+#   FIX-C  RANGE GUARDS RELAXED: the original code used df['GSR'].between(0,4095)
+#          which discards most of the real sensor range (0–40952).  Corrected to
+#          the actual hardware range.  PPG guard widened to 40–200 bpm.
+#
+#   FIX-D  EEG RANGE: original code required EEG >= 0 but many band-power
+#          columns normalised to 0–1.  Guard now between(0.0, 1.0); if the CSV
+#          stores raw counts (> 1) the guard is auto-bypassed.
+#
+#   FIX-E  EPOCH COUNT / EARLY STOPPING:
+#            • EarlyStopping patience raised so training actually runs long enough
